## {{ rule.title }}

[26 U.S.C. § 63](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section63&num=0&edition=prelim) defines taxable income as adjusted gross income minus the standard deduction (or, if you itemize, minus itemized deductions plus the qualified business income deduction). For [Form 1040](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1040) line 15, the engine subtracts the standard deduction from AGI and floors at zero — you can't have negative taxable income.

Your AGI from US25-07 is **{{ rule.inputs_by_key["us.stage.adjusted_gross_income"].value | money(currency="USD") }}**. The 2025 standard deduction for your filing posture is **{{ rule.inputs_by_key["us.constants.standard_deduction"].value | money(currency="USD") }}**. Subtracting gives **taxable income of {{ rule.outputs[0].value | money(currency="USD") }}** — the base for both regular tax (US25-09) and the [§ 904](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section904&num=0&edition=prelim) foreign tax credit limitation fraction (US25-12).

